On the other hand, the discriminator is trying its best to detect whether its fake or real

So the goal of the generator is to make the discriminator think that the output it produced is the real data as much as possible - so you can imagine the loss function containing the discriminator as a function of the input

Then once we do that, we can train the generator, which works by taking some random input (like some noise distribution) and feeding it in the generative model which will produce an output that we can then feed into the discriminator
